ly white women, can play in the new political and cultural order.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCommonwealth literature (English)xWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aDecolonization in literature. 0aImperialism in literature. 0aNational characteristics, British, in literature. 0aWomen and literaturezEnglish-speaking countriesxHistoryy20th century. 4aGender Studies. 4aLiterary Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171143540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501711435423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501711435/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles